es off. But since the journey along the curve can be lengthy, it=E2=80=99s =
hard to predict which firms will emerge as the winners and losers. During t=
he commercialization of the internet, many of the ultimate winners didn=E2=
=80=99t emerge until after the dot-com bubble had burst, in 2000. (Google w=
as founded in 1998, but it didn=E2=80=99t go public until 2004. Facebook wa=
sn=E2=80=99t created until 2004, Airbnb until 2008.) There is no guarantee =
that history will repeat itself. But investors who are still riding the A.I=
